President Biden visited the Portland Air National Guard Base in Portland, Oregon, where he spoke about the investments being made to modernize American airports and infrastructure. He thanked local leaders and members of Congress for their support in passing the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law and highlighted the importance of investing in the country's airports, ports, and rail systems. The President also addressed the issue of inflation and the rising gas prices, attributing them to the disruptions caused by the COVID-19 pandemic and Vladimir Putin's gas price increase. He called on Congress to pass legislation to lower the cost of utility bills and prescription drugs. President Biden expressed optimism about America's potential and emphasized the need to build a better and more resilient country.